procstep.procdesc: The following steps were performed by ESRI: Extracted eur_p.shp from AND Global Road Data. Copied all boundary features inside water bodies from Europe Major Water. Removed water body features. Corrected the projections for several islands with data from World Vector Shoreline. Combined nation and province codes as the common attribute and joined each of the three provincial lookup tables to the data set. Aggregated Estonia and Denmark second-level divisions to create first-level divisions by matching the higher-level divisions in ESRI Data & Maps 2004 Europe data. Added three attributes, PROV1, PROV2, and PROV3, and coded them by combining province and country names. Corrected coding errors. Summarized on each attribute, PROV1, PROV2, and PROV3, and merged features to create each of the three province-level shapefiles. For each of the three new shapefiles, updated some values for CNTRYABBR attribute, added and coded attributes SQKM and COLORMAP, and rearranged and renamed the remaining attributes. Created ArcGIS® layer files (.lyr), projection files (.prj), and spatial indices.

dataqual.logic: No duplicate features are present. The shapefile is converted to SDC (Smart Data Compression) format in ArcSDE®. This verifies and validates the geometry.
dataqual.complete: After processing, the data set is checked for drawing display and number of records and file sizes compared with source materials.
